mystery /ˈmɪstərɪ/

(mysteries) 

1. N-COUNT A mystery is something that is not understood or known about. 迷 

例： The source of the gunshots still remains a mystery. 枪弹来自何处依然是一个迷。 

2. N-UNCOUNT If you talk about the mystery of someone or something, you are talking about how difficult they are to understand or know about, especially when this gives them a rather strange or magical quality. 神秘 (性) 

例： She's a lady of mystery. 她是一个神秘的女人。 

3. ADJ A mystery person or thing is one whose identity or nature is not known. 来历不明的 [ADJ n] 

例： The mystery hero immediately alerted police after spotting a bomb. 那个不知名的英雄发觉炸弹后马上报了警。 

4. N-COUNT A mystery is a story in which strange things happen that are not explained until the end. 悬疑 (推理) 故事 

例： His fourth novel is a murder mystery set in London. 他的第4本小说是一个以伦敦为背景的凶杀疑案。

</div>

